formattedAddress: 5/F., The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C
location.address: 5/F., The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: Fantastic Indian food. All of the grill menu is excellent, particularly the lamb chops. Restaurant decor is really interesting & staff are friendly. Hard to get a table @ dinner, lunch is much easier.
Nice little neighbourhood bar. Small, friendly staff. Good happy hour. Pilsner Urquell & Peroni on tap. Free WiFi - password: crispy32

location.address: No.32, Second Street,Sai Ying Pun, Sheung Wan
formattedAddress: No.32, Second Street,Sai Ying Pun, Sheung Wan

tip.text: High class fine dining. Suckling pig was a fantastic dish, along with the squid and chorizo starter. Desserts were also excellent. Pricey, but highly recommended.

location.address: 16 St. Francis Yard, Wanchai, Hong Kong
formattedAddress: 16 St. Francis Yard, Wanchai, Hong Kong

tip.text: Cold cuts & starters were excellent. Pasta was quite good, but not quite brilliant. Really enjoyed the buzzy atmosphere. Staff were really friendly & nice, but service was a bit slow.

location.address: 16 St. Francis Yard, Wanchai, Hong Kong
formattedAddress: 16 St. Francis Yard, Wanchai, Hong Kong

tip.text: It's a decent burger, but a bit overrated at that price. Duck fat fries were nice. But I thought the best thing there was the ice cream cookie sandwich. Also notably lacking in their choices of beer.
This place is closing on August 7th. Food was pretty good, inventive, but not mind blowing for the price. Nice atmos, but too loud to hear the copious amounts of details that come with every dish.

formattedAddress: 3/F, Lyndhurst Tower, 1 Lyndhurst Terrace (at Wellington Street)

tip.text: Afternoon tea set was excellent, scone and then a good selection of savoury and sweet snacks. Setting was lovely and worth a visit.
Nice bar with good views. Service was a bit slow though. Happy hour till 8pm with free snacks & but 1 get 1 free on selected drinks. Their Cosmopolitan was nice, but more of a Cosmo martini!
Maternity clothing store with a wide selection. Offers a lot of fashionable choices for the pregnant lady. Staff are really nice.
It's not bad, though sushi @ Terminal 1 is better. Decent stop to get your final sushi fix before you leave Tokyo. Still a lot better than the food you get at the Cathay lounge, but then that's free.

venue.name: 寿司田 成田空港店

tip.text: Shio style with a light broth flavoured by scallops & chicken. I had the dipping noodles & they were nowhere near as nice as Rokurinsha nextdoor. Ok ramen, but I think the worst so far on the street.

venue.name: Hirugao (塩ラーメン専門店 ひるがお 東京駅店)

tip.text: Best ramen I've had. Creamy, rich, meaty tsukemen broth, with a separate bowl of thick noodles. Complete noodle nirvana. At the end you can request an extra ladle of light broth creating a light soup.

location.crossStreet: 東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート
formattedAddress: 丸の内1-9-1 (東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート)

tip.text: Road lined with loads of sakura trees. Looks amazing in the evenings when they are in full bloom. In season they block cars from coming down so you can come have a picnic under the beautiful trees
Fantastic teppanyaki restaurant. Great choices: steak, chicken & seafood. Loved everything they cooked. Spicy cod roe rice, sirloin steak & yuzu octopus were excellent. English menus, great staff.
Interesting tanmen style ramen. All bowls come topped with a decent portion of veggies. Deluxe version had thickly sliced pork and the runny egg. I preferred their chicken karage to their gyoza.

formattedAddress: 丸の内2-7-3 (東京ビル TOKIA B1F)

venue.name: 東京タンメン トナリ 丸の内店

tip.text: Ox tongue ramen is their specialty. Light but meaty broth with lots of spring onion and wood ear fungus. Meat was very tender. Beef tongue gyoza were also great. They also have normal pork ramen too.

formattedAddress: 7/F, South West Tower, Convention Plaza, 1 Harbour Rd

tip.text: Amazing amazing food here. Calves liver on cauliflower puree (specials menu) was excellent. All complimented by excellent sherries.
Really lovely & quaint small railway town with a little gift shop. The bigger tour busses don't seem to visit Jing Tong and that means it is a bit quieter and less commercial. Worth visiting.

venue.name: 菁桐鐵路故事館 Jing Tong Railway Story House

tip.text: Hotel restaurant, and hotel prices - quite expensive. Quality is ok but I've eaten better Japanese at cheaper close by.
The seafood here is truly amazing. Go for the top level set menu (TWD 2280 / person) and you'll have the greatest seafood meal of your life.

venue.name: 煮海 Trésors de la Mer

tip.text: Really good brunch here. Tripe sandwich was excellent, and the fries were perfect. Other dishes like the burger & chilli looked really good. Selection of draft & bottle beers were excellent.

venue.name: EIEIO Gastropub (咿呀咿呀呦新美式酒館)

tip.text: See if you can get on the Hello Kitty Eva airlines flight! Pointless but cute.

venue.name: Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport (TPE) (臺灣桃園國際機場)

tip.text: Lamb chops on mash was very good. Tender and tasty lamb.

tip.text: Seafood Don is amazing. Tasty rice with great texture served with perfectly presented heaps of fish and seafood.
